A little about me, .. .. .. .. my name is Anthony Mosley and I am the founder of HE'S ABLE PROFESSIONAL CLEANING. Though a Texas native, I have come to call Oregon my home. The saying, "If you don't like the weather, wait 5min" has proven itself to be true time and time again. 
 
I am a strong believer in making a difference, a difference within myself and a difference within my community. We never really know the full impact of a simple smile or just friendly words of encouragement can have on someone. Happiness is a choice, prosperity is a mindset and a lifestyle. HE’S ABLE CLEANING is built on Faith! The faith to change and help lives, the faith to change and help a community. As we know, life can be very interesting and all within a moments time it can completely change! I've witnessed firsthand the effects self-doubt and unbelief. I grew-up in Galveston, TX in public assistance housing. We rarely had food to eat, and bills where always passed due. Continuously  our power was shut-off and we had no electricity to stay warm so as a family we would have to wear all of our clothes at once and sleep in a huddle. I've seen the hopelessness of individuals who've given-up on life and the fruit that a productive life can provide.
 
At a young age I made a promise to myself to not reproduce what I was born into. I told myself that it's not about how I start, it's about how I finish. I know that all things are possible to those who believe. So I have challenged myself to soar as high in life as I've been down.
 
My journey wasn't and has never been perfect or easy, but it was well worth it. I believe in the greatness of a dream and what faith in that dream can birth in ones life. Many times I’ve wanted to give up and settle for the mediocre of life, settle for the averages of life. But the faith in my dream wouldn't let me throw in the towel.
 
I see that people need a voice of reason, an individual that has seen the worst of life but refused to bow to it's influences, but still pressed forward and refused to not become a product of my environment. I've heard so many times, "You don't know what it's like to be me and you haven't been through what I’ve been through" .. .. .. the many stories I've heard people tells themselves for not going after their dreams. Just through the fear of failing. I choose to make a differnce, I choose to giveback to the very people who helped me. I desire to produce a business that can employ anyone and everyone.
 
So, now looking back over my life and I know from firsthand experience the it’s not how you start the journey, it's how you finish.
